### Discussion Points

This section summarizes key strategic and technical discussions about the project's direction.

*   **Dataset Strategy:** Initial attempts to use a real-world dataset from Kaggle were unsuccessful due to unstable/broken links. We have pivoted to generating our own synthetic data, which is a robust and academically sound approach that unblocks development.
*   **AI Strategy:** The core AI feature will be time-series prediction for occupancy. We explicitly decided against computer vision to keep the project scope focused and avoid implementation complexities.
*   **Database Architecture & Security:** The current single-database approach with strong, role-based access control is secure, scalable, and aligns with industry best practices.
*   **Project Constraints:** The project must not incur any hardware or software licensing costs. All development will use free, open-source software.

